What I genuinely dislike:

The shell pattern is over-engineered for the wrong problem. You solved "fast first paint" perfectly — the page loads instantly. But you created a dashboard where users must click twice to see any actual data. A DBA opening this at 7am doesn't want to read "Open Cost Overview when bill movement, Cortex spend, or contract risk needs proof." They want to see the numbers. The shells feel like a loading screen dressed up as a feature. For executives who visit weekly, the shells are fine. For operators who visit hourly, they're friction.

The 10 sections with 60 workflows create analysis paralysis. This dashboard tries to be everything: an executive briefing tool, an operational control room, a FinOps platform, a security posture monitor, an architecture governance system, AND a DBA triage tool. No single product can serve all these audiences well without becoming a portal nobody loves. The ambition is admirable but the result is sprawl. Pick three sections that are world-class instead of ten that are good.

The configuration is ALFA-specific throughout. Warehouse lists, database patterns, role mappings, company names — all hardcoded. This will never be reusable for another Snowflake customer without a complete rewrite of config.py. If this is only for ALFA, that's fine. But the code pretends to be multi-tenant when it's really single-tenant with a Trexis sidecar.
